&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Howdy! Before you apply, please give this job description a thorough read.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Grounded experience selling into pharma, specifically patient services and access teams, is a MUST have.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you think you’ll be stretched, you will be (a situation we’d like to avoid-smile).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cover letters are appreciated and read (by a human).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;100% remote and must be US based.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The brainchild of David Ricks, CEO of Lilly, and incubated by Boston Consulting Group’s Digital Ventures, PrescriberPoint is a Series A healthtech firm (L.P.s Lilly, Pfizer, Adobe, MasterCard) focused on helping HCPs reduce the time, tension, and anxieties they and their patients encounter during the prescribing journey. We offer an end-to-end AI-enabled solution that includes drug awareness and education, medical affairs content, real-time coverage and affordability tools, PA support, and patient start programs, including Sampling.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a dynamic and results-oriented Director of Business Development with pronounced experience in selling technology to the commercial pharmaceutical industry. Reporting directly to the CEO/CRO, the ideal candidate will be responsible for driving sales growth of our leading-edge Patient Services solutions. This role requires tested consultative selling skills, in-depth knowledge of commercial infrastructure, strong understanding of current technologies, and the ability to effectively position product features, benefits, and value to diverse stakeholders.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sales Execution:&lt;/strong&gt; Generate, pursue and close opportunities focusing on key decision-makers from patient services, market access, brand, and marketing teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sales Presentations:&lt;/strong&gt; Conduct engaging presentations and product demonstrations, highlighting the benefits and value of our solutions geared to the specific functional needs of our clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Negotiation:&lt;/strong&gt; Negotiate contracts and pricing agreements to maximize profitability while ensuring customer satisfaction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt; Work closely with cross-functional teams, specifically marketing, to develop brand-specific presentations and proposals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Maven&lt;/strong&gt;: Serve as a data denizen, intentionally updating, leveraging, and proactively evolving our CRM system (Hubspot) and related AI tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Knowledge:&lt;/strong&gt; Developing a robust understanding of our solutions and how they impact our client’s needs and metrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Competencies:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communication Skills&lt;/strong&gt;: Excellent verbal, written, and presentation skills. Ability to present ideas clearly and persuasively using a variety of formats to different audiences, including executives, clients, and team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consultative Selling&lt;/strong&gt;: Ability to creatively sell complex solutions by understanding and navigating sophisticated sales journeys; can pivot pitches based on objections without fluttering an eyelash&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Relationship Building&lt;/strong&gt;: Exceptional networking skills to build and maintain relationships with key stakeholders, partners, clients , and internal staff.

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hello! Please give this job description a thorough perusal before you decide to apply. There are aspects that will immediately knock you out of contention and we don&#39;t like raising hopes unnecessarily. For example, the ability to Claude code alongside engineers (Python/JS, LLMs/eval frameworks strongly preferred), Prior Auth domain knowledge, strong product-data prowess (SQL-querying), etc., Again, give it a good review. The fit may not be there.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cover letters are welcomed, appreciated, and reviewed (by a human).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applicants must reside in the States.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt; 100% Remote w/ occasional in-person meetups &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;strong&gt;Comp:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt; $110–$130k + bonus (DOE &amp;amp; location)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who is PrescriberPoint?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PrescriberPoint, a Series A startup incubated by BCG Digital Ventures and funded by Lilly, Pfizer, MasterCard, and Adobe, is modernizing how U.S. healthcare professionals (HCPs) get patients on therapy. Our platform streamlines prescribing by bringing together trusted drug information, coverage and prior authorization requirements, patient affordability options, and practice tools—while enabling compliant collaboration with pharmaceutical brand teams. PriorAuth is our flagship AI-powered workflow automation platform, transforming healthcare case management from manual processes to intelligent, automated conversations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Be Doing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll own execution and outcomes for PriorAuth—our AI-powered prior authorization and case management platform—within the product strategy set by the Director of HCP Product. Your north star: shape an intelligent, automated product experience for the HCPs and clinical staff who submit prior authorizations, with a relentless focus on automation and AI-enablement that reduces manual effort and earns their trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll work from a Jobs-To-Be-Done mindset to deeply understand clinical workflows (eligibility checking, PA form completion, medical necessity letters, case tracking) and translate those jobs into experiences powered by agentic AI. You&#39;ll ship production code alongside engineering—building features and supporting experiments hands-on—and stay close to the data, reporting on how the product is used so we can focus our investment on scaling and growth. You&#39;ll partner closely with engineering leads across each workstream, design, and AI/data science to deliver production-ready AI that reduces administrative burden while ensuring clinical safety and compliance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Achieve (Outcomes)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shape the prior authorization experience:&lt;/strong&gt; Help shape an intuitive, trustworthy product experience for HCPs and clinical staff submitting prior authorizations—making a historically painful workflow feel simple.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advance automation &amp;amp; AI-enablement:&lt;/strong&gt; Move PA workflows toward intelligent, agentic experiences—identifying where automation and AI can remove steps, surface answers, and speed decisions for clinical teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build &amp;amp; ship:&lt;/strong&gt; Ship production code alongside engineering—delivering features and standing up experiments that move the PA experience forward.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Report on product &amp;amp; data usage:&lt;/strong&gt; Instrument the product and report on how it&#39;s used, turning usage and adoption signals into a clear view of where to focus for scaling and growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Protect trust &amp;amp; compliance:&lt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hello! While we love outliers, we expect you to have the following baseline experiences to apply: successes in marketing to HCPs and Pharmaceutical Brands; institutional and specialty pharmacy exposure is a visceral plus, as is having digital agency prowess. Must be AI fluent. Strongly suggest reviewing the entire JD before making the decision to give us the gift of your time.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cover letters are welcome, appreciated, and reviewed by a human.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Must be U.S. based; 100% remote with occasional in-person appearances; sadly we can’t support Visas.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About PrescriberPoint&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PrescriberPoint is Series A healthtech, funded by Lilly, Pfizer, Adobe, and MasterCard, on a mission to make the prescription journey painless for healthcare providers (HCPs) and patients through an end-to-end solution. Our platform powers 35,000+ pharmaceutical microsites and prescribing tools, including a powerful agentic prior authorization product, generating 500,000+ HCP visits monthly, primarily through sophisticated digital marketing campaigns.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re seeking a strategic and very hands-on VP of Marketing, reporting directly to the CEO, to scale and lead our marketing function across two critical pillars: our Digital Agency and Corporate Marketing. This is a foundational leadership role perfect for someone who thrives in early-stage environments and wants to shape marketing from the ground up in the healthtech space.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Own&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Digital Agency&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll provide strategic leadership and hands-on experience to our internal digital agency that serves pharmaceutical clients (HCPs) and related products and markets. This means inspiring and leading the delivery of integrated, cutting-edge digital marketing campaigns that promote our comprehensive platform and powerful prescribing tools to HCPs. Working with the Agency’s Director, you’ll partner closely with Sales and Customer Success to ensure alignment of expectations and consistent delivery against SLAs, manage client onboarding processes, and collaborate with pharmaceutical MLR (Medical, Legal, Regulatory) teams to de-risk marketing content. As a trusted advisor to clients, you&#39;ll translate their objectives into actionable marketing programs while maintaining relentless focus on ROAS. You’ll also collaborate with internal Sales, Business Development, Product, and Data Analytics teams to continually evolve digital marketing strategies spanning the full funnel from awareness-building to target identifiability and conversion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Corporate Marketing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Build our brand and awareness throughout our ecosystem, which includes HCPs, manufacturers, institutions, specialty pharmacies, and the investment community through strategic conference participation, educational webinars, social media engagement, and coordination of a PR contractor. You&#39;ll drive high-quality MQL generation that converts into partnership opportunities and sales conversations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Leadership &amp;amp; Innovation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide executive level guidance of the marketing function; can advocate and defend positions with grace and ease&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay at the forefront of AI-enabled marketing innovations that advance both client and our goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive a continuous improvement and testing culture to maintain competitive advantage&lt;/li&gt;
